I Tested EVERY Hyped AI Tool - I ONLY Kept Using These
1.2KLikes
41,065Views
Jul 142025
Join me as I chat with Ras Mic to discuss the top AI tools (claude code to n8n), evaluating each as overrated or underrated: 00:00 - Intro 01:32 - n8n 06:35 - LindyAI 07:31 - Claude Code 12:09 - Devin/Code Rabbit 19:56 - Bolt/Lovable/Tempo 23:12 - Figma Make/Hostinger/Airtable 27:25 - ManusAI 30:10 - VAPI 31:08 - MCP 35:46 - Vibe Coding Profitable SaaS 51:11 - GitHub Key Points: • Ras Mic and I evaluate various AI tools as "overrated" or "underrated," including n8n, String, Claude Code, Devon, and CodeRabbit • They discuss the potential of MCP (Multi-Context Protocol) and its impact on non-technical users • They analyze Greg's viral tweet about building a $50K/month SaaS business using AI tools • Ras Mic provides a simple GitHub crash course explaining branching and workflow best practices Get Your Complete Financial OS at https://www.brex.com/sip 1) n8n & Automation Tools The consensus: UNDERRATED for technical folks, overrated for everyone else. If you understand technical concepts but don't code, these tools unlock MASSIVE potential • String is building "prompt-to-automation" on top of Pipe Drive • Lindy AI offers 100+ templates that spark ideas for automation The future of automation is prompt-based. No more manual workflow building! 2) Claude Code: The ULTIMATE Coding Agent This might be the most underrated tool we discussed. "If I had to pick one for the rest of my life, it's Claude Code" - @RasMic Why it's a game-changer: • Builds its own task list • Creates its own plan • Writes tests automatically • True agentic coding Yes, it requires using a terminal (scary for non-coders), but the payoff is WORTH IT. 3) Devin & CodeRabbit: The TRUE Assistants These tools are changing how real products get built: Devin's best features: • DeepWiki: Contextualizes your entire codebase • Integrates with Slack/Linear tickets • Creates PRs automatically "For anyone building something serious with a small team, this alone is worth whatever Devin is charging" - @RasMic 4) The GitHub Workflow for Non-Techies Think of GitHub as one giant line representing your project: • Main branch = your live, working code • New branches = where you build new features safely • Merging = adding tested features to your main product This is how REAL products are built without breaking what's already working! The future of vibe coding tools will make this workflow accessible to everyone. 5) The $50K/Month SaaS Reality Check We discussed my viral tweet about building a $50K/month SaaS with vibe coding. The truth: • It's not EASY, but it's more POSSIBLE than ever • The paradigm has shifted - building takes weeks not years • "Pessimists are often right, but optimists make money" Is it probable? No. Is it possible? ABSOLUTELY. 6) The Developer Mindset Divide We noticed an interesting pattern in how people react to ambitious goals: • CTOs (technical folks): "Here's why it's hard" • CEOs (visionaries): "Here's why it's possible" The best companies need BOTH mindsets to succeed. But as non-technical people start building products with AI tools, we're about to see who's really about it! 7) MCP (Multi-Context Protocol): Money Context Protocol Despite developer skepticism, MCP is HUGELY underrated for non-technical folks. Why it matters: • Allows AI to access external information with minimal setup • Integrates third-party services into your AI workflows • Creates true assistant-like experiences The M in MCP might as well stand for MONEY. Notable Quotes: "Cloud Code is the truest form of agentic coding we've ever experienced." - Ras Mic "If there was any time to start something that has the slightest chance of being successful, there's no better time than today." - Ras Mic LCA helps Fortune 500s and fast-growing startups build their future - from Warner Music to Fortnite to Dropbox.
